---
name: Festival Restrictions
history:
- Created by Proposal 7833 (ais523), 5 December 2016
text: |
  While Agora's Festivity is nonzero, the following apply:

  (a) Non-Festive players are never considered Supporters of a
      dependent action;

  (b) Non-Festive players cannot flip the Imminence of any
      proposal;

  (c) Quorum for Agoran Decisions is equal to half the number of
      Festive players, rounded up;

  (d) Each Festive player has the maximum possible voting
      strength. All other players have the minimum possible voting
      strength.

  While Agora's Festivity is zero, the paragraphs above have no
  effect and are ignored.
id: 2481
rev: 0
power: 2.1
annotations: []
